Class WarehouseRegister

  • java.lang.Object
    • WarehouseRegister
  • public class WarehouseRegister
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the warehouseregister, which is responisble for containing all the items.

    The warehouseregister is expected to:

    • Return all items in the warehouse.
    • Get an item from the warehouse by the itemnumber.
    • Add a new item to the warehouse.
    • Increase the quantity of an item by the itemnumber.
    • Decrease the quantity of an item by the itemnumber.
    • Remove an item from the warehouse by the itemnuber.
    • Change the price and set discounts of an item by itemnumber:
      • Set discount in percent.
      • Set discount in kr, norwegian kroner.
      • Set new price.

      • findItemByItemNumber

        public Item findItemByItemNumber​(java.lang.String itemNumber)
        Returns the item found in the warehouseregister with the corresponding itemnumber. Since every item has an uniqe itemnumber, is it either none or one matching item to each itemnumber.

        If the itemnumber does not match any item, null is returned.

        Parameters:
        itemNumber - The itemnumber of the item to search for.
        Returns:
        The item matching the itemnumber. If no item was found, or the parameter is invalid, null is returned.
